# Belt-and-suspenders cache-control override for the PWA service worker and
# manifest. Vite copies files from public/ into dist/ at build time. Netlify
# reads this file natively; some other hosts (including Vercel derivatives)
# ignore it, which is fine — the primary fix is the `updateViaCache: 'none'`
# flag on `navigator.serviceWorker.register()` in src/main.tsx.
#
# Without these headers, mobile PWAs can end up stuck on a stale version for
# days because the CDN serves a cached copy of /sw.js and registration.update()
# byte-compares the cached copy to itself. See Gotcha #31 in CLAUDE.md.

/sw.js
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=0, must-revalidate
  Service-Worker-Allowed: /

/manifest.webmanifest
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=0, must-revalidate

/workbox-*.js
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=0, must-revalidate

/version.json
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=0, must-revalidate
